box": [117.8, 394.5, 313.6, 418.8]}, {"text": "6%", "bbox": [920.4, 398.0, 945.0, 422.3]}, {"text": "6%", "bbox": [1029.3, 398.0, 1053.9, 422.3]}, {"text": "Ultimate projected increase (a)", "bbox": [117.8, 424.0, 337.4, 448.3]}, {"text": "5%", "bbox": [920.4, 427.6, 945.0, 451.8]}, {"text": "5%", "bbox": [1029.3, 427.6, 1053.9, 451.8]}, {"text": "Year of ultimate projected increase (a)", "bbox": [117.8, 453.6, 391.9, 477.9]}, {"text": "2039", "bbox": [902.6, 457.1, 939.5, 481.4]}, {"text": "2025", "bbox": [1011.5, 457.1, 1048.4, 481.4]}, {"text": "(a)", "bbox": [112.2, 491.8, 132.3, 511.2]}, {"text": "During 2015, we revised our retiree trend assumption to reflect our experience and future expectations for changes in the cost of medical coverage, including", "bbox": [145.5, 491.8, 1061.4, 511.2]}, {"text": "a longer grade down period to the ultimate rate.", "bbox": [145.5, 509.5, 426.5, 529.0]}, {"text": "These assumed health care cost trend rates have an impact on the retiree medical plan expense and liability,", "bbox": [112.2, 537.9, 1063.3, 567.1]}, {"text": "however the cap on our share of retiree medical costs limits the impact. A 1-percentage-point change in the", "bbox": [112.2, 564.5, 1063.2, 593.7]}, {"text": "assumed health care trend rate would have the following effects:", "bbox": [112.2, 591.1, 683.5, 620.3]}, {"text": "1%", "bbox": [885.6, 638.9, 910.2, 663.2]}, {"text": "Increase", "bbox": [864.8, 657.4, 930.9, 681.6]}, {"text": "1%", "bbox": [994.5, 638.9, 1019.1, 663.2]}, {"text": "Decrease", "bbox": [973.0, 657.4, 1040.7, 681.6]}, {"text": "2015 service and interest cost components", "bbox": [117.8, 683.4, 430.1, 707.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [852.7, 686.9, 861.9, 711.2]}, {"text": "4", "bbox": [933.3, 686.9, 942.5, 711.2]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [961.6, 686.9, 970.9, 711.2]}, {"text": "(3)", "bbox": [1036.1, 686.8, 1057.6, 711.2]}, {"text": "2015 benefit liability", "bbox": [117.8, 713.0, 272.7, 737.2]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [852.7, 716.5, 861.9, 740.7]}, {"text": "40", "bbox": [924.1, 716.5, 942.5, 740.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [961.6, 716.5, 970.9, 740.7]}, {"text": "(36)", "bbox": [1026.8, 716.4, 1057.6, 740.7]}, {"text": "Savings Plan", "bbox": [112.2, 763.1, 232.3, 792.8]}, {"text": "Certain U.S. employees are eligible to participate in 401(k) savings plans, which are voluntary defined", "bbox": [112.2, 799.5, 1063.4, 828.6]}, {"text": "contribution plans. The plans are designed to help employees accumulate additional savings for retirement,", "bbox": [112.2, 826.1, 1063.2, 855.2]}, {"text": "and we make Company matching contributions for certain employees on a portion of eligible pay based on", "bbox": [112.2, 852.7, 1063.2, 881.8]}, {"text": "years of service.", "bbox": [112.2, 879.3, 256.8, 908.4]}, {"text": "Certain U.S. salaried employees, who are not eligible to participate in a defined benefit pension plan, are", "bbox": [112.2, 922.5, 1063.2, 951.7]}, {"text": "also eligible to receive an employer contribution to the 401(k) savings plan based on age and years of service", "bbox": [112.2, 949.1, 1063.2, 978.3]}, {"text": "regardless of employee contribution.", "bbox": [112.2, 975.7, 437.2, 1004.9]}, {"text": "In 2015, 2014 and 2013, our total Company contributions were $148 million, $130 million and $122 million,", "bbox": [112.2, 1019.0, 1063.2, 1048.1]}, {"text": "respectively.", "bbox": [112.2, 1045.6, 223.4, 1074.7]}, {"text": "For additional unaudited information on our pension and retiree medical plans and related accounting policies", "bbox": [112.2, 1088.8, 1063.2, 1117.9]}, {"text": "and assumptions, see “Our Critical Accounting Policies” in Management’s Discussion and Analysis of", "bbox": [112.2, 1115.4, 1063.3, 1144.5]}, {"text": "Financial Condition and Results of Operations.", "bbox": [112.2, 1142.0, 529.5, 1171.1]}]}